Document: TextureButton
Path: godot/classes/class_texturebutton.rst
Summary: Defines the properties available for the TextureButton class in Godot Engine.

Properties
- flip_h (bool): If true, the texture is flipped horizontally. Default: false.
- flip_v (bool): If true, the texture is flipped vertically. Default: false.
- ignore_texture_size (bool): If true, the button's size is not determined by the texture size. Default: false.
- stretch_mode (StretchMode): Defines how the texture is stretched or tiled. Default: 2.
- texture_click_mask (BitMap): A BitMap used to define the clickable area of the texture.
- texture_disabled (Texture2D): The texture to display when the button is disabled.
- texture_focused (Texture2D): The texture to display when the button has focus.
- texture_hover (Texture2D): The texture to display when the mouse is hovering over the button.
- texture_normal (Texture2D): The texture to display when the button is in its normal state.
- texture_pressed (Texture2D): The texture to display when the button is being pressed.
