Document: TextureButton
Path: godot/classes/class_texturebutton.rst
Summary: Describes the properties of the TextureButton class in Godot Engine, including texture flipping, size handling, stretch modes, click masks, and various textures for different button states.

Inherits: BaseButton < Control < CanvasItem < Node < Object

Properties:

flip_h (bool): If true, texture is flipped horizontally.
Method: set_flip_h(value: bool)
Method: is_flipped_h() → bool

flip_v (bool): If true, texture is flipped vertically.
Method: set_flip_v(value: bool)
Method: is_flipped_v() → bool

ignore_texture_size (bool): If true, the size of the texture won't be considered for minimum size calculation, so the TextureButton can be shrunk down past the texture size. Default: false.
Method: set_ignore_texture_size(value: bool)
Method: get_ignore_texture_size() → bool

stretch_mode (StretchMode): Controls the texture's behavior when you resize the node's bounding rectangle. See the StretchMode constants for available options. Default: 2.
Method: set_stretch_mode(value: StretchMode)
Method: get_stretch_mode() → StretchMode

texture_click_mask (BitMap): Pure black and white BitMap image to use for click detection. On the mask, white pixels represent the button's clickable area. Use it to create buttons with curved shapes.
Method: set_click_mask(value: BitMap)
Method: get_click_mask() → BitMap

texture_disabled (Texture2D): Texture to display when the node is disabled. If not assigned, the TextureButton displays texture_normal instead.
Method: set_texture_disabled(value: Texture2D)
Method: get_texture_disabled() → Texture2D

texture_focused (Texture2D): Texture to overlay on the base texture when the node has mouse or keyboard focus. A partially transparent texture should be used to ensure the base texture remains visible. To disable the focus visual effect, assign a fully transparent texture. Note that disabling the focus visual effect will harm keyboard/controller navigation usability.
Method: set_texture_focused(value: Texture2D)
Method: get_texture_focused() → Texture2D

texture_hover (Texture2D): Texture to display when the mouse hovers over the node. If not assigned, the TextureButton displays texture_normal instead when hovered over.
Method: set_texture_hover(value: Texture2D)
Method: get_texture_hover() → Texture2D

texture_normal (Texture2D): Texture to display by default, when the node is not in the disabled, hover or pressed state. This texture is still displayed in the focused state, with texture_focused drawn on top.
Method: set_texture_normal(value: Texture2D)
Method: get_texture_normal() → Texture2D

texture_pressed (Texture2D): Texture to display on mouse down over the node, if the node has keyboard focus and the player presses the Enter key or if the player presses the shortcut key. If not assigned, the TextureButton displays texture_hover instead when pressed.
Method: set_texture_pressed(value: Texture2D)
Method: get_texture_pressed() → Texture2D